    {
      "id": "l7-phrases",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Buying phrases",
      "body": "# At the shop\n\nThree phrases for buying:\n\n- **How much does it cost?** (इसकी कीमत कितनी है?)\n- **It is too expensive.** (यह बहुत महँगा है।)\n- **I want to buy this.** (मैं यह खरीदना चाहता हूँ।)\n\nThe word **too** here means *more than you want* (ज़रूरत से ज़्यादा): *too expensive* = महँगा (a problem), not just *very*. To say something is fine, use **It is cheap** (यह सस्ता है)."
    },
    {
